<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-12T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-12T11:00:00-05:00" n="541" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/7–844:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-12T12:00:00-04:00">July 12,
                                    1944—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>5454. Your 5397, July 8, 5 p.m. Our views are given fully in Department’s
                            5420, July 10, midnight.</p>
                        <p>The <hi rend="italic">Aide-Mémoire</hi> now to be presented to the
                            Swedish Government refers to “any commitment for 1945 exports” and would
                            therefore cover the export of ball bearings, etc. It will not then be
                            necessary to present Swedes with <hi rend="italic">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                            referred to in Department’s 5338, July 6, repeated to Stockholm as
                            1347.</p>
                        <p>Sent to London repeated to Stockholm.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>